#Concept



#Configuration

    #ip nat inside
    #ip nat outside

    #ip access-list standard INSIDE_NAT_ADDRESSES
    #permit 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255
    
    
##Dynamic

**With a pool or via an interface:**

    #ip nat pool OTUSIDE_PUBLIC 208.92.153.5 208.92.153.6 netmask 255.255.255.252
    
    #ip nat inside source list INSIDE_NAT_ADDRESSES <interface|pool of addresses> int fa0/1 overload

**Dynamic NAT (no PAT) - leave out overload**


**Using an interface in the NAT command automatically selects IP addresseb configured on interface for inside global address**

    #show ip nat translation

##1-to-1 NAT

    #ip nat inside source static 192.168.1.51 208.92.153.5

##1-to-1 NAT with port forwarding/port translation

    #ip nat inside source static tcp 192.168.1.6 80 202.92.153.5 80
    #ip nat inside source static tcp 192.168.1.8 3389 202.92.153.5 3389